description: An ecosystem within a landscape defined as Karst topography characterized by caves, sinkholes, disappraring streams and underground drainage. Karst forms when groundwater dissolves pockets of limestone, dolomite, or gypsum in rock.[From the Houghton Mifflin Student Resource Center GeologyLink.:http://college.hmco.com/geology/resources/geologylink/glossary.html]
title: Karst Landscape
